6-08-27&amp;rft.isbn=9780195793871&amp;rft.aulast=Jafri&amp;rft.aufirst=Syed+Husain+Mohammad&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt16" id="mwAg0"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt16" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAg4"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-4" id="cite_note-4"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-4" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-4" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt17" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.alimamali.com/html/eng/index.html"},"title":{"wt":"Chapter IV Iamhood"},"author":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"date":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"website":{"wt":"Imam Ali (a.s.) Foundation"},"publisher":{"wt":"Imam Ali (a.s.) Foundation, an affiliate website of the Grand Ayatullah al-Sayyid Ali al-Hussani al-Sistani"},"access-date":{"wt":"24 December 2017"},"quote":{"wt":"Appointing the heir was done when the Prophet [P] returned from the (Departure Pilgrimage); he [p] gathered all the pilgrims in a place called (Ghadeer khum) addressing them with a lengthy speech through which he asked:(Do not I own thy souls more that thou do, they said: aye). Then he [p] took Imam Ali [p] by the shoulder, holding him in front of the people and said:(He whom I am his guardian, Ali be his guardian). Thus he [p] certified Imam Ali&apos;s [p] heavenly guardianship; so everybody who was present then paid tribute to him, including the second Caliph ( i. e Omar Ben Al-Khattab), who congratulated Ali [p] saying: (Blassed be thee O! Ali, thou became my guardian and the guardian of every Mo&apos;men.)"},"archive-url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20171211173515/http://www.alimamali.com/html/eng/index.html"},"archive-date":{"wt":"2017-12-11"},"dead-url":{"wt":"no"},"df":{"wt":""}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAg8"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.alimamali.com/html/eng/index.html" id="mwAhA">"Chapter IV Iamhood"</a>. <i id="mwAhE">Imam Ali (a.s.) Foundation</i>. Imam Ali (a.s.) Foundation, an affiliate website of the Grand Ayatullah al-Sayyid Ali al-Hussani al-Sistani. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171211173515/http://www.alimamali.com/html/eng/index.html" id="mwAhI">Archived</a> from the original on 2017-12-11<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAhM">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAhQ">24 December</span> 2017</span>. <q id="mwAhU">Appointing the heir was done when the Prophet [P] returned from the (Departure Pilgrimage); he [p] gathered all the pilgrims in a place called (Ghadeer khum) addressing them with a lengthy speech through which he asked:(Do not I own thy souls more that thou do, they said: aye). Then he [p] took Imam Ali [p] by the shoulder, holding him in front of the people and said:(He whom I am his guardian, Ali be his guardian). Thus he [p] certified Imam Ali's [p] heavenly guardianship; so everybody who was present then paid tribute to him, including the second Caliph ( i. e Omar Ben Al-Khattab), who congratulated Ali [p] saying: (Blassed be thee O! Ali, thou became my guardian and the guardian of every Mo'men.)</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Imam+Ali+%28a.s.%29+Foundation&amp;rft.atitle=Chapter+IV+Iamhood&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.alimamali.com%2Fhtml%2Feng%2Findex.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt17" id="mwAhY"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt17" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAhc"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-5" id="cite_note-5"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-5" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-5" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt18" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://www.al-islam.org/articles/beliefs-did-prophet-s-appoint-successor"},"title":{"wt":"Beliefs: Did the Prophet (s) Appoint a Successor"},"last":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"first":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"date":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"website":{"wt":"Al-Islam.org"},"publisher":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"access-date":{"wt":"25 December 2017"},"quote":{"wt":"The Shi&apos;ah believe that the proclamation mentioned by the Qur&apos;anic verse was fulfilled by the Prophet (s) when he appointed Imam &apos;Ali bin Abi Talib (a) as his successor on the day of Ghadir Khumm."},"archive-url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20171225203104/https://www.al-islam.org/articles/beliefs-did-prophet-s-appoint-successor"},"archive-date":{"wt":"2017-12-25"},"dead-url":{"wt":"no"},"df":{"wt":""}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAhg"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.al-islam.org/articles/beliefs-did-prophet-s-appoint-successor" id="mwAhk">"Beliefs: Did the Prophet (s) Appoint a Successor"</a>. <i id="mwAho">Al-Islam.org</i>. <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171225203104/https://www.al-islam.org/articles/beliefs-did-prophet-s-appoint-successor" id="mwAhs">Archived</a> from the original on 2017-12-25<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAhw">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAh0">25 December</span> 2017</span>. <q id="mwAh4">The Shi'ah believe that the proclamation mentioned by the Qur'anic verse was fulfilled by the Prophet (s) when he appointed Imam 'Ali bin Abi Talib (a) as his successor on the day of Ghadir Khumm.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Al-Islam.org&amp;rft.atitle=Beliefs%3A+Did+the+Prophet+%28s%29+Appoint+a+Successor&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-islam.org%2Farticles%2Fbeliefs-did-prophet-s-appoint-successor&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt18" id="mwAh8"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt18" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAiA"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-6" id="cite_note-6"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-6" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-6" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt19" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://ismailignosis.com/2015/07/07/imam-ali-declared-the-successor-of-prophet-muhammad-in-sunni-hadith-literature/"},"title":{"wt":"Imam Ali declared the Successor of Prophet Muhammad in Sunni Hadith Literature"},"author":{"wt":"Mawlana Hazar Imam"},"date":{"wt":"&lt;!--Not stated-->"},"website":{"wt":"Ismaili Gnosis"},"publisher":{"wt":"Ismaili Gnosis"},"access-date":{"wt":"25 December 2017"},"quote":{"wt":"As you know, the Shi&apos;a divided from the Sunni after the death of Prophet Muhammad. Hazrat Ali, the cousin and son-in-law of the Prophet, was in Shia belief, named by the Prophet to be the Legitimate Authority for the interpretation of the faith. For Shi&apos;a today all over the world, he is regarded as the first imam."},"archive-url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20171226020706