ifier" id="mwAkw">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1163%2F2211-2685_eco_SI.100" id="mwAk0">10.1163/2211-2685_eco_SI.100</a>. <q id="mwAk4">The terms "Sunnism" and "Sunni" are anglicizations of Arab. ahl al-sunnah (the people of the Sunna [lit. "custom, way"]) or ahl al-sunnah wa-l-jamāʿa (the people of the Sunna and community).</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Sunnism%2C+Sunni&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Christianity+Online&amp;rft.pub=Brill&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1163%2F2211-2685_eco_SI.100&amp;rft.au=Lucas%2C+Scott+C.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt68" id="mwAk8"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt68" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAlA"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-12" id="cite_note-12"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-12" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-12" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt38" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.thefreedictionary.com/Sunnism"},"title":{"wt":"Sunnism"},"work":{"wt":"-Ologies &amp; -Isms"},"publisher":{"wt":"The Gale Group"},"access-date":{"wt":"Oct 5, 2016"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAlE"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.thefreedictionary.com/Sunnism" id="mwAlI">"Sunnism"</a>. <i id="mwAlM">-Ologies &amp; -Isms</i>. The Gale Group<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAlQ">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAlU">Oct 5,</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2