les" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAmc"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-15" id="cite_note-15"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-15" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-15" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt41" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"author1":{"wt":"George W. Braswell"},"title":{"wt":"What You Need to Know about Islam &amp; Muslims"},"date":{"wt":"2000"},"publisher":{"wt":"B&amp;H Publishing Group"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-8054-1829-3"},"page":{"wt":"62"},"edition":{"wt":"illustrated"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAmg">George W. Braswell (2000). <i id="mwAmk">What You Need to Know about Islam &amp; Muslims</i> (illustrated ed.). B&amp;H Publishing Group. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAmo"> </span>62. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAms">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAmw"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-8054-1829-3" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8054-1829-3" id="mwAm0">978-0-8054-1829-3</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=What+You+Need+to+Know+about+Islam+%26+Muslims&amp;rft.pages=62&amp;rft.edition=illustrated&amp;rft.pub=B%26H+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8054-1829-3&amp;rft.au=George+W.+Braswell&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt41" id="mwAm4"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt41" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAm8"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-16" id="cite_note-16"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-16" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-16" class="mw-reference-text">An Introduction to the Hadith. John Burton. Published by Edinburgh University Press. 1996. p. 201. Cite: "Sunni: Of or pertaining <i id="mwAnA">sunna</i>, especially the <i id="mwAnE">Sunna</i> of the Prophet. Used in conscious opposition to Shi'a, Shi'í. There being no ecclesia or centralized magisterium, the translation 'orthodox' is inappropriate. To the Muslim 'unorthodox' implies heretical, <i id="mwAnI">mubtadi</i>, from <i id="mwAnM">bid'a</i>, the contrary of <i id="mwAnQ">sunna</i>, and so 'innovation'."</span></li><li about="#cite_note-17" id="cite_note-17"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-17" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-17" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/crcc/engagement/resources/texts/muslim/reference/glossary/term.SUNNAH.html" id="mwAnU">Sunnah</a> <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20101205042656/http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/crcc/engagement/resources/texts/muslim/reference/glossary/term.SUNNAH.html" about="#mwt63" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"webarchive","href":"./Template:Webarchive"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20101205042656/http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/crcc/engagement/resources/texts/muslim/reference/glossary/term.SUNNAH.html"},"date":{"wt":"2010-12-05"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAnY">Archived</a><span about="#mwt63" id="mwAnc"> 2010-12-05 at the </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine" about="#mwt63" id="mwAng">Wayback Machine</a><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Webarchive_template_wayback_links" about="#mwt63" id="mwAnk"/>, Center for Muslim-Jewish Engagement</span></li><li about="#cite_note-18" id="cite_note-18"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-18" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-18" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt71" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Hughes"},"first1":{"wt":"Aaron"},"title":{"wt":"Muslim Identities: An Introduction to Islam"},"page":{"wt":"115"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=95jSBFFaDkUC&amp;pg=PA115"},"quote":{"wt":"It is a mistake to assume, as is frequently done, that Sunni Islam emerged as normative from the chaotic period following Muhammad&apos;s death and that the other two movements simply developed out of it. This assumption is based in... the taking of later and often highly ideological sources as accurate historical portrayals – and in part on the fact that the overwhelming majority of Muslims throughout the world follows now what emerged as Sunni Islam in the early period."},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-231-53192-4"},"date":{"wt":"2013"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAno">Hughes, Aaron (2013). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=95jSBFFaDkUC&amp;pg=PA115" id="mwAns"><i id="mwAnw">Muslim Identities: An Introduction to Islam</i></a>. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAn0"> </span>115. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAn4">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAn8"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-231-53192-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-231-53192-4" id="mwAoA">978-0-231-53192-4</a>. <q id="mwAoE">It is a mistake to assume, as is frequently done, that Sunni Islam emerged as normative from the chaotic period following Muhammad's death and that the other two movements simply developed out of it. This assumption is based in... the taking of later and often highly ideological sources as accurate historical portrayals – and in part on the fact that the overwhelming majority of Muslims throughout the world follows now what emerged as Sunni Islam in the early period.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Muslim+Identities%3A+An+Introduction+to+Islam&amp;rft.pages=115&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-231-53192-4&amp;rft.aulast=Hughes&amp;rft.aufirst=Aaron&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D95jSBFFaDkUC%26pg%3DPA115&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt71" id="mwAoI"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt71" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAoM"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-19" id="cite_note-19"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-19" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-19" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt72" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Hughes"},"first1":{"wt":"Aaron"},"title":{"wt":"Muslim Identities: An Introduction to Islam"},"page":{"wt":"116"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=95jSBFFaDkUC&amp;pg=PA115"},"quote":{"wt":"Each of these sectarian movements... used the other to define itself more clearly and in the process to articulate its doctrinal contents and rituals."},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-231-53192-4"},"date":{"wt":"2013"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAoQ">Hughes, Aaron (2013). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=95jSBFFaDkUC&amp;pg=PA115" id="mwAoU"><i id="mwAoY">Muslim Identities: An Introduction to Islam</i></a>. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAoc"> </span>116. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAog">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAok"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-231-53192-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-231-53192-4" id="mwAoo">978-0-231-53192-4</a>. <q id="mwAos">Each of these sectarian movements... used the other to define itself more clearly and in the process to articulate its doctrinal contents and rituals.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Muslim+Identities%3A+An+Introduction+to+Islam&amp;rft.pages=116&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-231-53192-4&amp;rft.aulast=Hughes&amp;rft.aufirst=Aaron&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D95jSBFFaDkUC%26pg%3DPA115&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASunni+Islam" class="Z3988" about="#mwt72" id="mwAow"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt72" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAo0"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-20" id="cite_note-20"><a href="./Sunni_Islam#cite_ref-20" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-20" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt74" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"author":{"wt":"Tore Kjeilen"},"url":{"wt":"http://lexicorient.com/e.o/ali.htm"},"title":{"wt":"Lexic Orient.com"},"publisher":{"wt":"Lexic Orient.com"},"date":{"wt":""},"accessdate":{"wt":"2011-06-05"},"archive-url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20110605031233/http://lexicorient.com/e.o/ali.